delta analysis

library(tidyverse)
D<-function(f,delta=.001) {
  fun=function(x){
  (f(x+delta)-f(x))/delta
  }
  return(fun)
}

Hypothesis: \(\delta\) is around e-8

1. \(f(x)=e^{x}\)

f = function(x) {exp(x)}

df=D(f,delta = 10^-(1:20))
e=abs(df(0)-1)
x=c(1:20)
plot(x,log(e), xlab = "delta=10^-x")

df=D(f,delta = ((1:100)*10^-9))
e=abs(df(0)-1)
x=c(1:100)
plot(x,log(e), xlab = "delta=x*10^-9")

e=abs(df(0)[1:20]-1)
x=c(1:20)
plot(x,log(e), xlab = "delta=x*10^-9")

0.8e-8

f = function(x) {exp(x)}

df=D(f,delta = (.5+((1:100000)/100000))*10^-8)
e=abs(df(0)-1)
x=c(1:100000)
plot(x,log(e))

df1 = data.frame("delta"=c((.5+((1:100000)/100000))*10^-8), "e"=e)
df1 %>% 
  arrange(e) %>% 
  head()
##         delta            e
## 1 8.80230e-09 8.382184e-14
## 2 1.27741e-08 1.136868e-13
## 3 1.36328e-08 2.687850e-13
## 4 1.19154e-08 5.513368e-13
## 5 7.94360e-09 5.515588e-13
## 6 9.66100e-09 6.058487e-13

consistent with 0.8e-8
